messages.content:
THOUGHT: The SLP vectorizer is incorrectly forming a vector compare on a narrower type (i16) when the original scalar compare operands were extended to i32, changing semantics. To prevent this, I will modify the compare compatibility check to ensure operand types match and are not narrowed. By requiring the operand types to be equal (and consistent with base operands when provided), the SLP will avoid vectorizing such mismatched compares.

```bash
perl -0777 -i -pe 's/(static\s+bool\s+areCompatibleCmpOps\(Value \*BaseOp0, Value \*BaseOp1, Value \*Op0,\s*Value \*Op1, const TargetLibraryInfo \*TLI\)\s*\{)/$1
  Type *Ty0 = Op0->getType();
  Type *Ty1 = Op1->getType();
  if (Ty0 != Ty1)
    return false;
  if (BaseOp0 && BaseOp1) {
    if (BaseOp0->getType() != Ty0 || BaseOp1->getType() != Ty1)
      return false;
  }
/s' llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && submit-patch
```

